---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const lastUpdated = '2026-06-15';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms"
  description="The rules for using Verified Software Bases — what we promise, what we don't, and what you agree to when you buy a Base."
>
  <section class="container-page pt-14 pb-8 md:pt-20">
    <p class="kicker">Terms</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-fg sm:text-5xl text-balance">
      The rules of the marketplace.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-3 font-mono text-xs text-faint">Last updated {lastUpdated}</p>
  </section>

  <section class="container-page pb-24 max-w-3xl">
    <div class="space-y-8 text-[16px] text-muted leading-relaxed text-pretty">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-fg">1. What you're buying</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You're buying a Base: a verified working software starting point. The
          specific deliverable depends on the tier — Use It (compiled app or
          access), Own It (source code), Remix It (a scoped customisation),
          Launch It (deployment help), Managed Hosting (recurring).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-fg">2. License</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Default buyer license: <span class="text-fg">you own your purchased copy.</span>
          You can modify, deploy, and use it commercially. You can't redistribute
          the unchanged source as a competing listing, can't claim affiliation
          with named alternatives, and must respect any third-party API or
          service terms baked into the Base. Per-Base licenses on the listing
          page may add or relax terms; the listing wins on conflict.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-fg">3. What we promise</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 marker:text-accent">
          <li>Every listed Base was reviewed and worked at the time of its <span class="text-fg">last verified</span> date shown on the listing.</li>
          <li>The deliverable described in the tier you purchased will be sent to your email within 7 days for manual fulfillment, or immediately if the listing is marked instant.</li>
          <li>If we can't deliver, we refund — see <a class="link text-accent" href="/refund">refund policy</a>.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-fg">4. What we don't promise</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 marker:text-accent">
          <li>That a Base will fit your specific use case beyond what its listing claims.</li>
          <li>Unlimited support, customization, or rewrites — those are tiered (Fix Pack / Remix / Launch).</li>
          <li>Uptime or SLAs unless you're on Managed Hosting, where its specific terms apply.</li>
          <li>That third-party services the Base integrates with (Supabase, Stripe, Resend, …) will keep their pricing or terms.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-fg">5. Creator obligations</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If you submit a Base, you confirm you have the right to license its
          contents to buyers, that the listing copy is accurate, and that the
          declared limitations are honest. We may remove listings that fail
          re-verification or violate the trust standard.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-fg">6. Prohibited use</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Don't use the marketplace, an API, or a Base to harass, deceive,
          violate someone else's terms, or build something illegal in your
          jurisdiction. We reserve the right to refuse service.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-fg">7. Liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          To the extent allowed by law, our total liability for any claim is
          capped at the amount you paid for the relevant Base in the past 12
          months. The marketplace is provided "as is".
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-fg">8. Changes</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          When these terms materially change, we update the date at the top.
          Continued use after a material change means you accept the update.
          If you don't, email us and we'll refund any unredeemed tier.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-fg pt-4 border-t border-line">
        Questions: <a class="link text-accent" href="mailto:sarthakagrawal927@gmail.com">sarthakagrawal927@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
